[6/21/2016][Start where you are. Use what you have. Do what you can][就地开始，用你所有的，做你所能做的] -Arthur Ashe
[1][we should confine the discussion to the question at issue.][我们应该将讨论的范围限制在这一有争议的问题上]
[2][I am calling to make an appointment with Dr. Hardy][我打电话是想和哈迪医生约个时间看病]
[3][The lawyer warned his client against testifying, but he did it anyway.][这名律师警告他的当事人不要出庭作证，但他还是这么做了] warn against 警告...不要, 提醒...提防
[4][If your advice had been acted upon, you would not have got into trouble.][如果我们的建议被采纳，你就不会惹上麻烦了] 

act upon 按照，对 ... 起作用

get into trouble 陷入困境, 惹上麻烦

[5][Tom very often take a nap for an hour after lunch.][汤姆常在午饭后小睡一小时。]

